"My hotel was empty and I thought, 'it's a simple idea to give it to the staff. ' "

The full text is 2,514 words and takes about 5 minutes to read

In order to provide free and convenient accommodation for the medical staff who are fighting against the epidemic, hundreds of people in the Wuhan Hotel Industry spontaneously formed the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Alliance on New Year's Eve (January 24) . As of 2100 hours on 30 January, the alliance had provided more than 40,000 overnight accommodations for 6,056 health care workers.

The 159 individual hotels, bed and breakfast, apartments and small hotel chains in the Wuhan area will no longer receive medical staff and guests from January 31, the alliance announced yesterday. Of the 112 other hotel chains, 62 will continue to provide accommodation for medical staff, with the exception of 50 that are already full.

In this regard, Beijing News reporter Dialogue Alliance first sponsor, hotel owner Xiao Yaxing, co-founder of global travel news founder Li Chao and the Alliance of Hotel Owners Rkatsiteli (not his real name) . It is reported that the alliance to stop part of the hotel reception, mainly due to the lack of urgently needed materials and financial resources, most of the hotel staff has been extremely tired, the hotel's materials and sanitary conditions also reached the limit. After that each hotel plan continues to receive the medical staff, may by oneself docking related hospital.

Volunteers deliver disinfectant to Alliance hotel. Photo courtesy of interviewees

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
━━━━━

Xiao Yaxing: After the union stops the part reception, the hotel, the hospital may by oneself docking

Beijing News: Why the Alliance support in the first place?

Xiao Yaxing: At that time, I felt that the medical staff were working too hard, many of them lived far away, and the transportation was not convenient. My hotel was empty, so I figured, you know, put it up for the paramedics. It's simple.

Beijing News: Why to stop part of the hotel reception work, what difficulties encountered?

Xiao Yaxing: lack of materials and funds, the government has no material support, disinfection work is also facing difficulties, at present mainly hotel staff or medical staff disinfection. Part of the hotel daily expenses are not small, have to bear, some can not bear, plus staff may not understand. We have roughly estimated that even if we stop some individual hotels, small hotel chains and other hospitality work, it should be able to meet the current demand.

Beijing News: At present still continues to receive the hotel, how to guarantee the material?

Xiao Yaxing: We have received a lot of donations from caring enterprises, and we will continue to provide material support to the remaining large hotel chains, including masks, protective clothing, body scanners, disinfectant and so on. There are 58 of the 200 suits left, and 3,000 of the second batch of 12,000 masks. Sterile water is now available in sufficient quantity. We're not gonNA raise money again. We could run out of supplies and shut down the alliance altogether.

Beijing News: After the end of the alliance, how to solve the problem of medical staff accommodation?

Xiao Yaxing: Even if the alliance stops, the hotel can continue to receive the medical staff, they can dock by themselves, but not through the alliance.

But remind them to pay attention to the disinfection work. In addition, our hotel chain is still in reception, after a series of supplies, will give priority to the hotel chain distribution, we will be better reception of medical staff. We also raised money for sleeping bags and body scanners, so we can donate them to Vulcan Mountain and Thor Mountain hospitals when they are ready.

Beijing News: How do you evaluate your behavior?

Xiao Yaxing: I don't want to read people's minds with the worst intentions. There are some remarks that make us feel cold, but very few, most of them are good. I would like to say to the participants of the alliance, everyone is very good, some hotels because of geographical location, transportation and other reasons, have not received after joining the medical staff, they are also very anxious, especially want to contribute. I think that by joining, we provide love, and we are a group that deserves to be remembered.

Li Chao: I want to help, that's all

Beijing News: Why to Launch Support League?

Li Chao: I want to help, that's all.

Beijing News: You drafted the notice to stop some hotel receptions. What was your mood at that time?

Li Chao: I stayed up late last night, and I had mixed feelings this morning when I saw the World Health Organization bulletin. For the past seven days, I've been on a roller coaster of anxiety, worry, excitement, and laughter. A group of US did a conscience, so much support and praise, the heart is still very happy.

Beijing News: To Stop Some hotel reception, mainly due to what considerations?

Li Chao: The reason is simple. It just doesn't work. Since the start of the alliance, many hotel owners have invested a lot of manpower and money. The estimated cost of water, electricity and linen is over 2.5 million yuan, not including room and labor costs. However, due to the lack of much-needed material and financial resources, the alliance's support for participating hotels is very limited, most of the hotel staff are extremely tired, and the hotel's material and sanitary condition is also reaching the limit, this puts the operation and service of the hotel at great risk.

Beijing News: WHAT'S NEXT FOR THE ALLIANCE?

Li Chao: The most important thing is to disinfect. With the consent of the hotel owners, the alliance will be unified arrangements for the disinfection of the above 159 hotels, the associated costs are covered by the alliance. Of the 112 other hotel chains, 62 will continue to provide accommodation for medical staff, with the exception of the 50 that are already full. We are also considering how to broaden the promotion channels for these hotels.

Volunteers deliver fund raising air purifier to the Alliance hotel. Photo courtesy of the respondents

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
RKATSITELI: I couldn't bear to stop the reception

Beijing News: Why did you participate in the alliance support?

Rkatsiteli: I saw a lot of the staff who had no place to live, and they were worried and tired, and some of them came to us in a panic, and I was too soft to say no.

Beijing News: Does Your Hotel Still Receive Health Care Workers?

RKATSITELI: Yes. On New Year's Eve, I joined the Contact Group of the alliance. Our two stores started the reception work. Since the first day of the New Year, 51 health care workers have been received in 35 rooms, and we are still receiving them.

Beijing News: How to disinfect the hotel every day?

RKATSITELI: There were clusters of staff in every hospital we connected to, and before we moved in, I would tell them that they had to do the disinfection themselves, because they were professionals. They need to bring their own four-piece sets, toiletries, garbage bags, the day to leave the store, garbage bags sealed, take away for disposal. Since we have a combination lock, the paramedics checked themselves in.

The public area of the whole building of the hotel is disinfected by myself, with diluted 84 disinfectant, the third day of the Lunar New Year Elevator, switch, door handle and so on all spray disinfection, and again tomorrow disinfection.

Beijing News: How much is the cost per day?

RKATSITELI: We're a commercial building, with commercial utilities, a room that costs about $20 a day, and rent.

Beijing News: Next Step if the cost can not afford, how to do?

RKATSITELI: Next we will look at the actual situation, if traffic in Wuhan is basically restored and it is easier for everyone to go home, I will communicate with the medical staff. In the area of cost, first of all, we will communicate with the landlord whether the rent can be reduced or not, and with the staff to communicate salary adjustment. In addition, we will also communicate with the medical staff to see if it is possible to charge a nominal amount of water and electricity charges, such as 10 yuan per day.

Beijing News: the Alliance today to stop part of the hotel reception work, you want to stop it?

RKATSITELI: I can't help it. It's not right if I don't receive them all of a sudden. The staff might not be able to find a place to stay.

Beijing News: How does it feel to participate these days?

White Feather: The idea is very simple, I have dozens of rooms can temporarily solve the medical staff accommodation difficult, I also do not have too much ability to organize, fund-raising materials, etc. .
